      • onLoadEnd

        void onLoadEnd(CefBrowser browser,
               CefFrame frame,
               int httpStatusCode)
        Called when the browser is done loading a frame. The frameIdentifer value will never be empty. Multiple frames may be loading at the same time. Sub-frames may start or continue loading after the main frame load has ended. This method will always be called for all frames irrespective of whether the request completes successfully.(${t_d67e99c7b437498eb7a691a5338ba33e})
        Parameters:
        browser - The corresponding browser.(${t_f7f667c60fba4f179276a572f61a627a})
        frame - The frame generating the event. Instance only valid within the scope of this method.(${t_34e6e5dd04da437ca84ede1d3d345d65})
        httpStatusCode - The status code of the load.(${t_ce893adff9a44e43afcb26e632c41cee})

      • onLoadStart

        void onLoadStart(CefBrowser browser,
                 CefFrame frame,
                 CefRequest.TransitionType transitionType)
        Called when the browser begins loading a frame. The frameIdentifer value will never be empty. Multiple frames may be loading at the same time. Sub-frames may start or continue loading after the main frame load has ended. This method may not be called for a particular frame if the load request for that frame fails. For notification of overall browser load status use onLoadingStateChange instead.(${t_a909d7bf1bdb4b3ab23fda32dbc3261a})
        Parameters:
        browser - The corresponding browser.(${t_21901ad29e734dc0bf6cb929f2de03d4})
        frame - The frame generating the event. Instance only valid within the scope of this method.(${t_a5ddcfe75524490cb957c420a2aaa02b})
        transitionType - The transition type.(${t_a9af5101d3b0425a9749510ee4164139})
